modules.description: Prints the current position in a source file to an output channel, parses a CSS selector from a lexing buffer while handling errors, and executes a parsing routine that processes the buffer and returns a modified key-value store. It operates on lexing buffers, hash tables of string-int pairs, and optional selector types. Used to analyze and transform CSS-like syntax during preprocessing or validation tasks.

Validates TailwindCSS class names at compile time using a custom parser built with ppxlib and menhir, identifies invalid classes with a spelling corrector algorithm, and supports arbitrary values in JIT mode. Processes string literals containing class name sequences and integrates with OCaml's syntax tree. Ensures type-safe usage of Tailwind classes in ReScript projects by catching errors during compilation.

Provides a mechanism for parsing and processing CSS-like syntax by analyzing lexing buffers, handling selector parsing with error detection, and modifying key-value stores. Operates on lexing buffers, hash tables, and optional selector types to transform or validate CSS structures. Can be used to track positions in source files, parse selectors, and update data stores during preprocessing. Enables low-level manipulation of CSS syntax for custom analysis or transformation workflows.
